{
  "doc_id": "60520",
  "text": "Four studies investigated how neighbourhood context was associated with perinatal health outcomes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and one longitudinal study focused on child accidents and injuries in children aged 0-5 years [CITATION_5] . Five studies analysed self-rated health or self-reported health problems [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] , and two of them considered a population sample 55 years or older [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] . One study focused exclusively on stress [CITATION_13] , one on smoking [CITATION_14] , one on heavy alcohol consumption [CITATION_15] and two on objectively measured coronary artery calcification in adults aged 45-75 years [CITATION_16] [CITATION_17] .",
